#castingcalls #greatbritishbakeoffmusical #casting #castingcall

The Brookside Theatre are looking for the last few 'contestants' to join their amazing cast for their charity production of THE GREAT BRITISH BAKE OFF MUSICAL 

Roles:

GEMMA (Female identifying - playing age 30s) Mezzo Belt.

A carer from Blackpool

BEN (Male identifying - playing age 30s/40s) Baritone/Tenor 

A widowed police officer from Bristol; single dad to Lily 

HASSAN (Male identifying - playing age 17-25) Baritone/Tenor - Needs to rap
An A-Level Student from London (Middle Eastern Heritage)

RUSSELL (Male identifying - playing age 45-70) Baritone/Tenor - Flamboyant aeronautic engineer

DEZZA (Male identifying - playing age 25-50) Baritone/Tenor

A Vegan who lives on a houseboat

Production runs 6th - 10th May 2026

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Lizzie Line / Free Parking)

Rehearsals: Monday & Wednesday evenings & Sunday daytimes by a schedule starting immediately at the theatre 

Profit Share production

If you are interested or know someone that might be right for any of these roles please get in touch either by PM or email casting@brooksidetheatre.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL:

Beneath the Waves: Chapter 1: Descension

A Kaiju Audio Drama

 

Hi Everyone,

I am currently in pre-production for a complete remake of my original college project that was massively expanded into a successfully Kickstarter funded sequel.

The Story revolves around a research team investigating a mysterious radiation leak of the west coast of Australlia; the team lead by Doctor Stevens are under an intense strain to reach the leak as soon as possible but find something much worse on their doomed voyage‚Ä¶

I am currently looking for someone to take the role of Captain Charlie Andrews, the owner of the Tugboat acquired for the expedition.

Full Character Bio:

CHARLIE ANDREWS: IRISH SAILOR, LATE 40‚ÄôS EARLY 50‚ÄôS. OWNER AND CAPTAIN OF THE BAD CRAB TUGBOAT OPERATING AROUND AUSTRALIA AT THE TIME OF THE EXPEDITION. BORN FOR THE SEA, MADE HIS BOAT HIS HOME, DOING ANY JOB THAT COMES HIS WAY. BUT A RECENT TRAGEDY HAS CAUSED HIM TO REFLECT BACK ON HIS TROUBLED LIFE.

The Character is very much inspired by Jared Harris‚Äô portrayal of Captain Mike in The Curious Case of Benjamin Button.

Casting Specifics:

¬∑         *Irish accent, not looking for any particular dialect as the character only refers to being ‚Äòfrom Ireland‚Äô as his more recent history is the subject of conversation. Any Irish accent will work but a native accent is preferred for authenticity.

¬∑         *Male, preferably aged 30-50 years old.

¬∑         *Must have access to their own recording equipment and be available to record from home.

Production Information:

¬∑         Production expected to commence in early March with planned release being 31st May 2026.

¬∑         The Final Product is Expected to be around 30-45 minutes in length.

¬∑         For more information on the pay; please enquire using the below contact details.

Additional Links:

¬∑         Beneath the Waves: Chapter II: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r5dJqfQ1lug](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r5dJqfQ1lug)

¬∑         Beneath the Waves (Original) [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_wWdvmEx-hw](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_wWdvmEx-hw)

Where to Contact Me:

Message me on my Facebook Page: [https://www.facebook.com/SamuelCollinsMM](https://www.facebook.com/SamuelCollinsMM)

Or

Email me at [s.collins158@gmail.com](mailto:s.collins158@gmail.com)

Notes:

¬∑         Please do not message me directly to my personal account, I won‚Äôt see them.

¬∑         The Attached Poster is still a work in progress.

We are in need of a visibly pregnant woman for our independent feature on Friday, February 13th in the Whitington area of Manchester. They will be needed for approximately 3 hours at a rate of ¬£40 per hour. We will be shooting a closeup shot of their stomach only - No acting experience required and their face won't appear on camera.

items.text:
# **CASTING CALL **

Hi,

I am Pragati Gupta, seeking actors for short scenes to be filmed for a graduate film directing class at UNCW.

Here is the breakdown for the ‚ÄúSorry We Missed You‚Äù scene recreation.

*Scene brief:* When a working-class father discovers his teenage son‚Äôs quiet rebellion, the family is forced to confront the cost of survival versus the promise of a better future.

**SEB**: 15-18 yrs old, (Male, Teenage son, Actors 18+ who can convincingly play younger are welcome.)

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì JENNY & POPPY (Newcastle)** 

We are currently casting **two key female roles** for a Newcastle-based short film / pilot being produced as part of a university project.

**Roles:**

**JENNY (mid - late 20s)**
Confident, sharp, and socially switched-on. Jenny is witty, emotionally intelligent, and often the voice of reason within the group. Strong presence on screen.

**POPPY (mid - late 20s)**
Warm, expressive, and empathetic. Poppy is thoughtful and emotionally open, with a grounded and natural energy. A character with depth and subtlety.

 **Location:** Newcastle (Bar No.28 & The Last Resort)
 **Shoot dates:** First two weeks of February (starting 4th Feb) ‚Äì approx. **6 days availability required**
 **Unpaid student production** (travel support available)
 Great **showreel material + headshots provided**

Submission ends 1st February.

If interested, please get in touch:

 willm.patton@gmail.com
 07495 605757

Feel free to share with anyone who may be suitable.

Thank you!

I can‚Äôt speak for all but I was involved in a few of them during and post covid! Often it involved individually recording live performers on a zoom call, and editing them together! A great example of it that is available is what Living Room Shakespeare did during covid: https://youtube.com/@livingroomshakespeareco.8383?si=gLd_0Gu9euukLnsq

Queer Shakespeare also continues to do this format! https://youtu.be/XL0-yHdb5Fo?si=WNzvh_jXazLxqSHj

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî ALT / GRUNGE GUYS ‚Äî PAID**
[ Los Angeles Locals Only ]

We're looking to cast x5 alternative/grunge guys to be part of short-form content that we are shooting for an independent artist. Not a high-budget project, but could be super cool to be a part of !!

**Date**: Tues Feb 10
**Platform**: TikTok / Instagram [ short-form shoot ]
**Role**: 'Alternative Guy'
**Location**: Indoor, Warehouse
**Compensation**: $120
**Commitment**: 2h, sometime in the afternoon
**Wardrobe**: To be coordinated with the director once you're casted.

**Apply via email *****with the following information*****:**
‚Äî Name + age range
‚Äî Location
‚Äî Recent photo
‚Äî Social media links
‚Äî Short selfie video (15-30 seconds) introducing yourself **

**Email To**: contact@meldemelo.com
**Subject**: Alt Guy Casting ‚Äî Feb 10th Short-form Shoot

*Please do not send me any other casting emails if you do not fit the casting call, as your email address will be blocked for future postings ***

The secret is out (a little earlier than planned)! Due to the incredible amount of interest we‚Äôve already received, NMD Productions is thrilled to announce that we are officially looking for talent for our upcoming first production this summer in Manchester.

We are currently casting for:
1 Principal Role
2 Supporting / Multi-role Spots

üåü Our Commitment to Casting

Unless otherwise stated, all roles follow gender, gender identity, and color-blind casting. We are looking for the best fit for the story, regardless of whether you are a seasoned professional or looking for your very first stage credit.

No experience? No problem. We are passionate about developing new and emerging talent. If you‚Äôve never been on stage before, we want to hear why you‚Äôre ready to start now!

üìÖ Key Dates

You must be available for the following performance dates in 2026:
Opening Night: July 31st
Main Run: August 5th ‚Äì August 9th
Evening Performances: Aug 5, 6, 7, & 8
Matinee Performances: Aug 8 & 9

üì© How to Apply

If you‚Äôre ready to hit the boards, please email teamnmdproductions@gmail.com with the following:
A recent headshot or selfie (one you are happy for us to use in promotional materials).
A summary of previous experience (or a brief note on why you want to be on stage if you‚Äôre new to acting!).

üé≠ The Audition Process

If invited to audition, please prepare:

A Comedy Monologue: This can be from a published play or any piece you can "inject the funny" into.
A Cold Read: On the day, you‚Äôll be given a scene to perform alongside a member of our current cast.

We know there is incredible talent in Greater Manchester and the North West, and we can't wait to see what you bring to the room. Keep an eye out for our Full Production Announcement on February 22nd!

Stu @ www.nmd-productions.co.uk

**TONIGHT: Queer Theatre Variety Night **
**Wednesday 4th February 2026**
üìçThe Two Brewers, Clapham

A proper queer night out, built around cabaret.

Expect a mixed bill of drag, stand-up, musical theatre, live music, spoken word, pop acts and queer cabaret. You‚Äôll see established performers sharing the best of their work alongside emerging artists stepping into the spotlight with something fresh.

With cabaret-style seating, it‚Äôs social by design. Come to watch, come to meet people, come to have a big joyful night in a queer-run room. And every ticket supports Queer Theatre‚Äôs work producing LGBTQIA+ stories and nurturing LGBTQIA+ theatre-makers.

**Cast:**
**Host: Jack Knave **‚òÖ Avital Kagan ‚òÖ Bobbi Dazzler ‚òÖ Bran Isabella ‚òÖ Dav Andrews ‚òÖ Fempath ‚òÖ Freddie Haberfellner ‚òÖ Lady Harmony Heaven ‚òÖ Josh Pullinger ‚òÖ Justin Elizabeth Sayer ‚òÖ Josh Sanchez ‚òÖ Pearl Does Country ‚òÖ Peter Pearl ‚òÖ Marsha Dean ‚òÖ Poet The Jules ‚òÖ Ri Baroche ‚òÖ Tooting Broadway ‚òÖ Yass Tina

üéüÔ∏è Tickets: ¬£20 all seats. Capacity: only 100 tickets. All profits support LGBTQIA+ theatre projects. All tickets include access to late-night cabaret and DJ after the show.

items.text:
CASTING ‚ÄúHillbilly Therapy.‚Äù

Think of Queer eye.  With Hillbillies.

6 homegrown ingenuous, southern rednecks give someone a life makeover.  Tackling living spaces to mindset with tricks and wisdom straight out of the backwoods‚Ä¶.  Blowing off steam, by blowing something up.  Camping in the woods as meditation, and building something wacky‚Ä¶ as art.

A heartwarming, blue collar comedy tour journey where not taking themselves seriously, helps them cope with serious life moments.

"Hillbilly Therapy." blends Larry the Cable guy elements of YouTube favorites‚Äîthink the spontaneity of David Dobrik, the wild antics of WhistlinDiesel, the humor of Ginger Billy, the cleverness of Mark Roper, and the heart of MrBeast. Together, we‚Äôre creating a show where we have a blast helping others.

We‚Äôre looking for individuals aged 21 to 75 from all walks of life. There‚Äôs no specific criteria on background, ethnicity, appearance or gender‚Äîwe just want Myth Busters chemistry. If you can pull off a Southern accent, that‚Äôs a bonus, but it‚Äôs absolutely not required.

"Hillbilly Therapy" will be semi-scripted Michael Reeves style. We‚Äôll have a storyline framework, but you‚Äôll have room to bring your own personality and humor into the scenes. 

First episode is a pilot to see how the concept lands, so we need people ready to have fun and collaborate.

If this sounds like you, we want to see your personality shine! Let‚Äôs help others‚Äîand have a blast doing it.

Please reply with a 1 to 2 minute video of yourself‚Ä¶.  Doing‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ (fill in blank here) 

Like‚Ä¶.

Applying for a fake job with a video interview‚Ä¶. to be a Realtor‚Ä¶ in a T-rex costume.

Or doing a cooking show‚Ä¶. With road kill.

Or make up something.

And send it as an attachment to this email:

anthonymorgali@gmail.com

Pilot Show pay is $250 / day.  

Non union.  Location:  Atlanta area.

Filming dates: Late March, early April 2026 - TBA

Thank you so much!!

Anthony Morgali

Show Runner

items.text:
Model | Performer | Wellness Professional
With over 80+ professional photoshoots under my belt ‚Äî including paid projects across fashion, lifestyle, artistic, body paint, and life modeling ‚Äî I have developed a versatile presence in front of the camera backed by a disciplined lifestyle and unique skillset. 

Height    195 cm  | 6.5
Weight  85kg | 187 pounds
Neck      40 cm  | 15.7 |
Chest    102 cm  | 40.2 |
Waist     78 cm  | 30.7 |
Hips.  96 cm |  37 |
Sleeve   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Inseam   81 | cm  | 31.9 |
Shoe Size  45  EU   | 10.5 UK
Skin Tone: Medium-light  
Eye Color: Brown 
Hair color: Dark brown 

Alongside modeling, I bring on-screen experience from multiple TV shows, interview formats, podcasts, and extra appearances in my home country, while continuously expanding into acting and performance-based work. 

Performance Skills
‚Ä¢ Aerial Acrobatics ‚Äî Hoop, Trapeze, Silks, Rope (Beginner‚ÄìIntermediate)
‚Ä¢ Contact staff ‚Äî Intermediate
‚Ä¢ Staff spinning - Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Katana/Aikido - Intermediate 
‚Ä¢ Yoga ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Swimming ‚Äî Advanced
‚Ä¢ Parkour - Intermediate+
‚Ä¢ Dance - freestyle freedom of expression intuitive improvised movement 
Some stage combat, shooting, falling experience 

Professional Background
‚Ä¢ Qualified Swimming Coach, Yoga Teacher, and Personal Trainer with 14+ years of teaching experience.
‚Ä¢ Deep expertise in health, movement, breath, wellness, and high performance. 

What Sets Me Apart
‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.
‚Ä¢ Holistic approach to self-regulation ‚Äî always camera-ready, physically prepared, mentally sharp, and adaptable.
‚Ä¢ Highly motivated in building my craft and presence ‚Äî I create, edit, and post content daily across YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram to develop audience. 

Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK, but open to international projects.
22

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì UPCOMING PSYCHOLOGICAL HORROR SHORT FILM | FENOMENON CREATIVE
Hello everyone,

We hope you‚Äôre doing well.

We are Fenomenon Creative, an independent filmmaking team from DFW, Texas, currently preparing our next untitled psychological horror short film on a micro-budget.

This film is a standalone pilot for a small, short-form anthology. I am looking to connect with NJ/NY based collaborators (DOP, AD, Screenplay consultant) who are serious about craft and deeply passionate about storytelling. 

Open to collaborators of all backgrounds. Local availability and commitment are key. 

If this resonates, please DM me and I will share more details!

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm seeking actors for the first episode in a comedy web series, *Vancouver I Think We Should See Other Cities*. It revolves around a young man navigating the surreal everyday life of the Canadian city.

This first episode titled ‚ÄúTurn Down The Heat‚Äù is surreal but also risqu√© in what I hope is the best way possible. It‚Äôs important to note that nothing of graphic nature is ever depicted onscreen. 

My number one priority is ensuring a welcome and safe environment where we are able to collaborate on a strong project. If you have any questions regarding the material before submitting, please DM me and I am more than happy to discuss. 

**Logline:**

A young man, Paul, goes to a meeting of the Hudson Williams Fan Club only to realize that he may be out of his depth.

**Production Details:**
* Location: Vancouver, BC
* Filming Dates: Latter half of February 2026 (TBD)
* Non-Union / Volunteer
* Food and IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**STEVEN - Male, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The charismatic leader of the Hudson Williams Fan Club.

**JULIA - Female, Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

A member of the Hudson Williams Fan Club. She is understanding and supportive to Paul when he needs it.

**HUDSON WILLIAMS FAN CLUB MEMBERS - Mid-Late 20s (Open Ethnicity)**

The rest of the group, unfazed by the events of the meeting. 

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to [vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com](mailto:vaithinkweshouldseeothercities@gmail.com)

Subject: ‚ÄúEPISODE #1 - [CHARACTER NAME]‚Äù
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo reel (if possible)
* Availability (Latter half of February 2026)

Thank you so much for your time. Take care and have a great day.

We're looking to cast x5 alternative/grunge guys to be part of short-form content that we are shooting for an independent artist. Not a high-budget project, but could be super cool to be a part of !!

So I just wanted to spread the word that Shon McGregory is a pedophile and not to cast him as an actor because he is unsafe. This is only one comment he made to me thinking i was 17 (I'm 42 but made a joke about being back in hs and all he saw was the age and said that he hoped my dad didn't inappropriately touch me as his kneejerk reaction to my age.)

üé¨ URGENT CASTING CALL ‚Äì DIASPORA SHORT FILM 

ROLE: THE PHOTOGRAPHER

We are currently casting for one remaining role in our short narrative film Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Set in 1970s Britain, Diaspora follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport. His encounter with a Balkan-born photographer becomes the emotional core of the film, as both men are forced to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. The story is intimate and character-driven, set largely within a photography studio, and relies on quiet tension, emotional restraint, and subtle performance.

We are looking to cast The Photographer, a Balkan or Eastern European man (playing age approximately 50s‚Äì70s) who has settled in Britain after leaving his homeland. The character is reserved, guarded, and shaped by lived experience. Acting experience is welcome but not essential; we are primarily interested in authenticity, presence, and emotional truth.

DETAILS:
- Shooting is scheduled for 22nd‚Äì26th February in Bristol
- Availability across these dates is required
- Applicants should be based in or able to stay locally in Bristol or nearby
- This is an unpaid student project, with travel expenses and food covered

The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

ROLE: THE PHOTOGRAPHER

We are currently casting for one remaining role in our short narrative film Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Set in 1970s Britain, Diaspora follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport. His encounter with a Balkan-born photographer becomes the emotional core of the film, as both men are forced to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. The story is intimate and character-driven, set largely within a photography studio, and relies on quiet tension, emotional restraint, and subtle performance.

We are looking to cast The Photographer, a Balkan or Eastern European man (playing age approximately 50s‚Äì70s) who has settled in Britain after leaving his homeland. The character is reserved, guarded, and shaped by lived experience. Acting experience is welcome but not essential; we are primarily interested in authenticity, presence, and emotional truth.

DETAILS:
- Shooting is scheduled for 22nd‚Äì26th February in Bristol
- Availability across these dates is required
- Applicants should be based in or able to stay locally in Bristol or nearby
- This is an unpaid student project, with travel expenses and food covered

KENT and SUSSEX AREAS
Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have parties, schools and events throughout the year.

You don't need a formal background in science as we teach you everything you'll need to know.

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins

items.text:
Friends!

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly The Colorado Film School) invites actors of all ages to participate in our Spring 2026 Open Auditions!

Our student filmmakers are casting for a wide range of short films, narrative projects, and cinematic productions, and we are seeking performers of all backgrounds, ages, and experience levels to help bring these stories to life on screen.

Whether you are a seasoned professional, a student, or someone who simply loves acting, you are warmly invited to audition and collaborate with the next generation of filmmakers.

üìÖ Audition Dates & Times

Friday, February 6, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 5:00 p.m.

Saturday, February 7, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 4:00 p.m.

 

üìç Location

Lowry Studios ‚Äì Community College of Aurora

9075 E. Lowry Blvd.

Denver, CO 80230

 

üé≠ What to Prepare

Please bring a 2‚Äì3 minute prepared monologue for your primary audition.

In addition to the main audition, we will also host Satellite Auditions for specific student film productions:

‚Ä¢ These will take place in rooms throughout the building

‚Ä¢ Auditions are first-come, first-served

‚Ä¢ Actors can sign up to cold read for individual projects

‚Ä¢ We anticipate up to 10 productions casting during this event

‚Ä¢ A list of roles and productions will be available on the day of the audition

‚Ä¢ Participation in satellite auditions is optional, but highly encouraged

 

üìù How to Sign Up

Actors can sign up using the QR code on the flyer or by visiting:

Accessible Web Link:

https://www.ccaurora.edu/open-auditions

(For visually impaired users or anyone unable to scan the QR code, this link provides full access to the sign-up form.)

If you can't find a reserved space that works for you, come anyway during your preferred time. We will work you into the schedule!

We can't wait to see you this Friday or Saturday!

 

üì© Questions?

Please contact:

galina.boulgakova@ccaurora.edu

 üé• Help our students tell their stories through the magic of cinema.

items.text:
Hello all, we are looking for actors for a CU Denver student film shooting this march 

Title: The Scare

Genre: Drama, Period 

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February

items.summary:
Hello all, we are looking for actors for a CU Denver student film shooting this march 

Title: The Scare

Genre: Drama, Period 

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February 

Shooting Schedule: ~mar 12-22 - 4 day shooting schedule will fall sometime within that time span depending on actor availability

Filming Location: Denver

If you are interested scan the QR code or email and reach out!

items.text:
**Castingaufruf f√ºr studentischen Kurzfilm (T√ºbinale)**

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen f√ºr einen ca. 6-min√ºtigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der T√ºbinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**M√§nnliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Au√üenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln k√∂nnen.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verl√§sslichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

items.text:
Hi all,
I am excited to announce that I am the director for an upcoming short film "Baller".

"Baller" is a short drama about a former professional footballer who projects his unfulfilled dreams onto his ten-year-old daughter - until he realises her happiness matters more than his legacy.

With the current crisis of youth teams picking up players younger than ever, "Baller" aims to spread awareness of this issue and the toxicity it can bring to parent-child relationships.

Any questions regarding this casting call or the project in general. Please feel free to send them to our email address:

BallerShortFilm@outlook.com

items.text:
**UNRAVEL** is a short psychological thriller exploring dissociation, betrayal, and the quiet violence of denial. The film is performance-led and naturalistic, prioritising subtle emotional storytelling over overt horror, with a strong focus on character and atmosphere.

 

**EDDY The  *****Husband***

**Production Type:** Short Film
**Playing Age:** 40‚Äì55
**Gender:** Male
**Accent:** British
**Ethnicity:** Any
**Location Required:** London / Surrey

**Shoot:** **1 day**
**Provisional Timing:** **Mid-March (dates TBC)**
**Remuneration:** **¬£100 for the day**

**Character Overview:**
Charming, distracted, and casually affectionate. Eddy hides a devastating secret. He must feel like a believable, loving husband until the truth explodes.

Strong naturalism and subtext-driven performance essential. Actor must be comfortable playing emotional concealment, intimacy, and sudden tonal shifts.

 

**ROBBIE  *****The Lover***

**Playing Age:** 30‚Äì45
**Gender:** Male
**Accent:** British
**Ethnicity:** Any
**Location Required:** London / Surrey

**Shoot:** **1 day**
**Provisional Timing:** **Mid-March (dates TBC)**
**Remuneration:** **¬£100 for the day**

Intense, physical, emotionally impulsive. Robbie is Eddy‚Äôs secret partner and the emotional fuse of the story.

Requires comfort with confrontation, intimacy, and high emotional stakes.

Please send your information to kate@pilgrimagepictures.uk

üé¨UNPAID CASTING CALL ‚Äî SITCOM ‚ÄúStake and Ale‚Äù
Final year University of York Film and TV students are currently casting for a Final Year Project ‚Äì  a Jacobean Sitcom ‚ÄúStake and Ale‚Äù

Stake & Ale is a classic sitcom with a 17th-century Jacobean twist! We follow the adventure of Bella Byrnes, a novice witch on the run from the witch trials, as she hides out in a failing tavern called The Ducking Stool.

Can she rally together the mismatched bar staff to get out of this scrape? Or will the ridiculous villain, the Witchfinder General, finally hunt her down?

ROLES

- BELLA BYRNES (mid-late 20s, female presenting)

- ALFIE TAVENER (late 20s-mid 30s, male presenting)

- MILDRED TAVENER (early-mid 30s, female presenting)

- LODWICK TAVENER (late teens-early 20s, male presenting)

- WITCHFINDER GENERAL (mid-late 30s, male presenting)

- SUSAN (late teens-early 20s, female presenting

All ethnicities welcome

Preferably Northern based

Key Info:

Filming Dates: Mon 20th April & Tue 21st April.

(And Mon 23rd March as well for Witchfinder General and Susan)

Rehearsal Dates TBC. 

Location: East Campus, University Of York 

Unpaid with travel/accomodation expenses covered. 

Lunch, snacks and drinks provided throughout the day. 

If interested, please email stakeandale@yahoo.com with:

- character of interest

- headshots

- showreel (if available)

- location 

by 9th February 2026.

Thank you!

items.text:
Hi all,
I am excited to announce that I am the director for an upcoming short film "Baller".

"Baller" is a short drama about a former professional footballer who projects his unfulfilled dreams onto his ten-year-old daughter - until he realises her happiness matters more than his legacy.

With the current crisis of youth teams picking up players younger than ever, "Baller" aims to spread awareness of this issue and the toxicity it can bring to parent-child relationships.

Any questions regarding this casting call or the project in general. Please feel free to send them to our email address:

BallerShortFilm@outlook.com

Hi all! I am casting for my final short film ‚ÄòBody Electric‚Äô with the University of Warwick and London Film School, shooting THIS WEEKEND üé• in Coventry! 

This film follows a young dancer as she navigates the absurdity of the world's indifference, finding that ‚Äúworking harder‚Äù is simply not enough for success. 

Snacks/ drinks will be provided on set. Transport may be compensated depending on distance. This is a great opportunity to add professional footage to your showreel and get on-set experience ‚ò∫Ô∏è Read below for specific role descriptions:

GIRL 1: 18-24, any ethnicity. As the coach‚Äôs daughter who gets the role over the protagonist, she‚Äôs talented and hardworking, but aware that her last name opens doors others have to fight to pry open. She doesn‚Äôt flaunt it, doesn‚Äôt apologize for it either. This is NOT a dancing role.

GIRL 2: 18-24, any ethnicity. Girl 1‚Äôs best friend. Warm, perceptive, and socially fluent. She smooths over conflicts, sometimes at the cost of her own voice. This is NOT a dancing role.

CROWD: A ‚Äúpressing, engulfing crowd‚Äù around the protagonist.

Snacks/ drinks will be provided on set. Transport may be compensated depending on distance. This is a great opportunity to add professional footage to your showreel and get on-set experience ‚ò∫Ô∏è Read below for specific role descriptions:

GIRL 1: 18-24, any ethnicity. As the coach‚Äôs daughter who gets the role over the protagonist, she‚Äôs talented and hardworking, but aware that her last name opens doors others have to fight to pry open. She doesn‚Äôt flaunt it, doesn‚Äôt apologize for it either. This is NOT a dancing role.

GIRL 2: 18-24, any ethnicity. Girl 1‚Äôs best friend. Warm, perceptive, and socially fluent. She smooths over conflicts, sometimes at the cost of her own voice. This is NOT a dancing role.

CROWD: A ‚Äúpressing, engulfing crowd‚Äù around the protagonist.

Required For |

Event: Wedding Exhibition Fair by Asiana Magazine

Where: üìç London, UK 

Date: Sunday 8th February 2026

Call Time Arrival and Wrap Time: 1:00PM till 4:00PM

K.A Global Production House is seeking a confident, bubbly, and professional Female Presenter to host interviews and provide news-style coverage at the Wedding Exhibition Fair organised by popular Royal Fashion Brand 'Asiana'. Interviewing the Exhibitors and briefly chatting to them asking them what their Brand/Business is about. 

This opportunity is ideal for those who are passionate about Fashion and Arts who want to build or expand their on-camera portfolio. At the function you are welcome to network for your own benefit which there will be high value individuals and groups from various professional backgrounds.

We also have lot's more functions coming up such as a private Charity Event taking place on 14th February 2026 and many other functions and projects. Which we will require a Presenter.

WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR?

Ages: 20's OR 30's

Fluent in English with strong voice projection

Naturally confident, energetic, and camera-friendly

Must be already based in London, UK or anyone who will be in London on that date and time

Interested in building experience, portfolio, credentials and industry connections

PLATFORM DISTRIBUTION |

Content Will Be Released On:

- Social Media Platforms

- YouTube

- K.A Global Homepage

Some Highlighted clips may be seen on South Asian Desi Television Network

WHAT YOU‚ÄôLL GAIN?

Added to K.A Global Casting Database

Support in building a professional portfolio

Introductions to Agents and Agency contacts

Consideration for future K.A Global projects, events and presenting roles

Opportunity to be considered as a Brand Ambassador

HOW TO APPLY?

Inbox The Following:

- Full Name

- Social Media Handles

- Portfolio 'If You Own One'

- Contact Information

Shortlisted applicants will receive a 5-minute phone call to discuss the event, interview style, and details.

SERIOUS APPLICANTS ONLY

Confirmed applicants for the 8th February event will be contacted Saturday morning (day before event).

The applicants not selected for this date may be contacted in advance for our 14th February 2026 Charity Event.

We are actively scouting long-term talents for upcoming projects and functions to join our team. We take Pride in those who have potential.

We would love to see lots of new talent, please do fill out the audition form if interested and send over your headshot/resume to the email provided. Any questions ask away below!

sharedPost.text:
AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare‚Äôs monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical r√©sum√© to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters‚Äô professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Lear‚Äôs eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Lear‚Äôs middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril‚Äôs partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Lear‚Äôs youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool ‚Äî Lear‚Äôs companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s‚ÄìLate 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear‚Äôs: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear‚Äôs descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Gloucester‚Äôs illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play‚Äôs violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìLate 30s
Gloucester‚Äôs legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as ‚ÄúPoor Tom‚Äù to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Goneril‚Äôs husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Regan‚Äôs spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril‚Äôs primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScHMbtYTBlReh1AvrRsYaDtGR0nPaMaNMleJO2BZIw-D4quWw/viewform?usp=header

LEAD ACTRESS CASTING CALL!!!

PRODUCTION: High School Series (being shot here in Georgia)

CASTING\LOOKING FOR - Lead Actress to portray the role of the girl best friend

CHARACTER CASTING - Samantha Dougal (16, Caucasian, is a sophomore in high school, athletic, medium build, average height, attractive in a cute nerd type of way, is an introvert, is part of the school yearbook staff, very shy when it comes to guys that she has a crush on, can be clumsy sometimes, very kind and considerate toward others, an empath, very intelligent, cares about others, doesn't think she's extremely attractive but feels she's pretty though, doesn't like to draw attention to herself)

QUALIFICATIONS - Must live in Georgia\based in Georgia, has reliable means of transportation, easy to work with, works well with others, has on set experience, is between the ages of 16 and 19\or in their early 20s & can come across as a high school student, has a look similar to the example photos listed below, will make themselves available for shooting days

OTHER DETAILS - Will be given footage to go toward their reel

If you're an actress in the Georgia or Atlanta area that would love to audition for this a Lead Actress Role, please reach out to the Director via his email listed below. Make sure to include best way of contact
* DIRECTOR's EMAIL - djbasic22@gmail.com

Hello everyone.  My name is Sage Christian Drake and I'm a documentary filmmaker. I'm planning to direct a micro short documentary (1-5 minutes long) and I need children ages 5-13 years of age, to write and read out loud to America.  The footage needs to be filmed on cellphone and shot anywhere in this country. I will be putting it together in jump cuts to make it sound like one letter being addressed. 

I have directed short documentary films including OUR SHOT and my documentary feature film MY EMPATHY, which won last year for Best Documentary Feature at the Zepstone International Film and Music Festival. 

You are more welcome to view my work and my current credits are listed on imdb.com. 

Completed film will be submitted to film festivals and eventually on YouTube viewing. 

Thank you and hope to hear from you soon.

NATIONALLY SYNDICATED COURT SHOW IS LOOKING FOR MARRIED & LONG-TERM COUPLES WHO WANT HELP OR CLOSURE

A nationally syndicated court show is seeking real married couples and long-term partners who are on the verge of breaking up and need answers, resolution, or closure.

We are especially interested in couples with years of history and real-life stakes, including shared children, finances, property, or businesses.

Are you and your spouse facing any of the following?

‚Ä¢ Are you married and ready to call it quits, but need answers first?

‚Ä¢ Do you suspect your spouse or long-term partner is cheating?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse accusing you of cheating and/or denying your child?

‚Ä¢ Have years of marriage led you to a breaking point where you need closure?

‚Ä¢ Do you have evidence your spouse or long-term partner has been unfaithful and want to confront them?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse‚Äôs behavior tearing your family or marriage apart?

‚Ä¢ Are bad habits or addictions damaging your marriage and affecting your children?

‚Ä¢ Have ongoing trust issues made it impossible to move forward in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are in-laws or extended family interfering in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are you in a long-term marriage with unresolved financial betrayal or disputes?

‚Ä¢ Are you married with children and need answers for the sake of your family‚Äôs future?

‚Ä¢ Have you reached the final straw in a long-term marriage and need resolution?

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Married couples

‚Ä¢ Engaged couples

‚Ä¢ Long-term couples (4+ years preferred) with real stakes involved

‚Ä¢ Shared children

‚Ä¢ Shared finances

‚Ä¢ Shared property (home, apartment, vehicles)

‚Ä¢ Shared business or major life commitments

‚Ä¢ LGBTQ+ married and long-term couples

WHAT‚ÄôS INCLUDED:

‚Ä¢ One-day court show appearance

‚Ä¢ Couples counseling / marriage counseling support

‚Ä¢ Lie detector testing (if applicable)

‚Ä¢ DNA testing (if applicable)

üëâ All testing and services are provided and paid for by production.

Click the link below or copy and paste to bowser 

[https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/](https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/)

I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**** We cannot dispute anything against councils - this would be a person to person claim - we have also reached out capacity for car cases and rogue traders ****

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**** We cannot dispute anything against councils - this would be a person to person claim - we have also reached out capacity for car cases and rogue traders ****

sharedPost.text:
AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare‚Äôs monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical r√©sum√© to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters‚Äô professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Lear‚Äôs eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Lear‚Äôs middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril‚Äôs partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Lear‚Äôs youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool ‚Äî Lear‚Äôs companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s‚ÄìLate 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear‚Äôs: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear‚Äôs descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Gloucester‚Äôs illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play‚Äôs violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìLate 30s
Gloucester‚Äôs legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as ‚ÄúPoor Tom‚Äù to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Goneril‚Äôs husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Regan‚Äôs spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril‚Äôs primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

We‚Äôre seeking real families or talent groups who naturally represent connection, joy, and everyday moments together.

**Who we‚Äôre looking for:**
* Families representing 2‚Äì3 generations
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 50+ 
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 30+ 
   * Children ages 5+
* All ethnicities encouraged to apply
* Comfortable on camera and able to interact naturally together
* Families together are welcome to apply, but if it‚Äôs just you individually please apply as well because we might be able to cast you together with others.

topComments.text:
I‚Äôm sorry but asking for a self-tape at the application stage is completely unprofessional. 

Self-tapes should only be requested once an application has been made and those who have been successful to the audition stage should be invited/requested to tape. 

Asking actors/actresses to send a self-tape in at the initial application is a waste of your time and most importantly the applicants time. It does not guarantee that the tapes will be watched or get a response. 

Self-tapes take a lot of effort and time to set up. From learning the lines, to setting up the camera, to getting the lighting right, editing it and sending it off. It‚Äôs a full time job in itself.

I have been a full time professional actor for 15 years and not once have I ever been asked to send a tape along with my initial application.

Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy or counselling session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. For this round of sessions we are planning both longer form scripted and shorter improv shoots.

We are currently especially interested in meeting actors who identify as queer or trans, and we are also very interested in actors who identify as Asian or latinx.

However, all ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are absolutely welcome.

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are February 3 to February 20, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

However, all ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are absolutely welcome.

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are February 3 to February 20, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.
